    "layoutDecisions": "The layout employs a vertical list to maximize screen real estate on mobile.  Sections are implicitly created through visual dividers and spacing between logically related settings. This top-to-bottom flow is intuitive and easy to scan.  Sufficient padding is used around elements to ensure comfortable tap targets for one-handed use.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user journey is straightforward: the user sees all settings, taps on a setting to modify it, and is given appropriate feedback (success/error messages). Irreversible actions (account deletion) have confirmation dialogs. Navigation is handled through top and bottom app bars, adhering to common mobile patterns.",
    "componentChoices": "The `appbar` component is used for top and bottom navigation, providing a consistent look and feel.  `list-item` components display individual settings with clear labels.  Input fields (`text input`, `text area`) are used where modification is needed. Switches (`switch`) are used for toggle settings. Buttons (`Button`) are used for actions like log out and account deletion.  A `dialog` (confirmation) is used before irreversible actions.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through spacing, padding, and consistent typography.  Section dividers enhance readability.  The use of clear labels and consistent design system components maintains a uniform visual style.  Important settings are not visually overemphasized to avoid cognitive overload."
  }
}
